'''薩吉德·賈偉德'''（{{lang-en|Sajid Javid}}，{{bd|1969年|12月5日|||catIdx=J}}）是[[英国保守黨|英国保守黨]]政治人物，现任英国[[英国卫生大臣|卫生与社会服务大臣]]。前[[德意志银行|德意志银行]]董事总经理，前任[[英国内政大臣|英国内政大臣]]、[[财政大臣_(英国)|财政大臣]]，现任[[英國下議院|英國下議院]][[布羅姆斯格羅夫_(英國國會選區)|布羅姆斯格羅夫議員]]，是为英国首位亚裔财政大臣。其内政大臣任内施政与其前任[[安珀·路德|安珀·路德]]相比较为软化。

賈偉德曾在2016年至2018年间任[[英国内阁|英国内阁]][[房屋、社區及地方政府事務大臣|社區及地方政府大臣]]、<ref>{{cite news|title=Coalition government and Labour reshuffle – the full lists|first=Paul|last=Owen|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/oct/07/coalition-government-reshuffle-the-full-list|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2013-10-07|accessdate=2013-10-07|archive-date=2018-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616001858/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/oct/07/coalition-government-reshuffle-the-full-list|dead-url=no}}</ref>2015至2016年任{{le|商业创新及技能大臣|Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills}}、2014年至2015年擔任{{le|文化傳媒及體育大臣|Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport}}、2014年擔任[[婦女及平等事務部長|平等事務部長]]、2013年至2014年出任[[財政部金融秘書|財政部金融秘書]]和2012年到2013年出任[[財政部經濟秘書|財政部經濟秘書]]。<ref>{{cite news |title=Coalition government reshuffle |first=Paul |last=Owen |url=http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/oct/07/coalition-government-reshuffle-the-full-list |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2013-10-07 |accessdate=2013-10-07 |archive-date=2015-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925072251/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2013/oct/07/coalition-government-reshuffle-the-full-list |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 早年生活 ==

贾维德出生在[[兰开夏郡|兰开夏郡]][[罗奇代尔|罗奇代尔]]的[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]裔家庭，兄弟五人。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/2014/04/sajid-javids-father-would-never-have-made-it-camerons-britain|title=Sajid Javid's father would never have made it into Cameron's Britain|first=George|last=Eaton|work=New Statesman|date=2014-04-14|accessdate=2015-11-22|archive-date=2015-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119154155/http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/2014/04/sajid-javids-father-would-never-have-made-it-camerons-britain|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://new.spectator.co.uk/2013/01/im-still-a-thatcherite/|title=Interview with Sajid Javid, the bus driver's son who may end up leading the Tories|first=James|last=Forsyth|work=The Spectator|date=2013-01-26|accessdate=2015-11-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123033754/http://new.spectator.co.uk/2013/01/im-still-a-thatcherite/|archivedate=2015-11-23}}</ref>其父为巴士司机。后来全家从兰开夏郡搬到英国西南[[布里斯托尔|布里斯托尔]]的斯台普顿路，因其父母在那里开了家商店，一家人住在商店上层两居室的公寓里。<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-43947008 |title=Who is Sajid Javid, the new home secretary? |date=2018-04-30 |work=''BBC News'' |accessdate=2018-04-30 |archive-date=2018-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613041556/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-43947008 |dead-url=no }}</ref>这家商店地处当地最声名狼藉的地区，贾维德曾开玩笑说小时候看到妓女就站在店外面。<ref name=javid-shop-anacdote>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/sajid-javids-rise-caps-triumph-of-five-brothers-b09z3mf3d |title=Sajid Javid’s rise caps triumph of five brothers |date=2018-05-06 |work=''The Times'' |accessdate=2018-08-02 |archive-date=2018-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802131905/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/sajid-javids-rise-caps-triumph-of-five-brothers-b09z3mf3d |dead-url=no }}</ref>在[[撒切尔夫人内阁|撒切尔政府]]施行私有化政策之后，青少年时期的贾维德对[[金融市场|金融市场]]产生了兴趣。十四岁时，他从银行借了500英镑投资[[股票|股票]]，还成为英国《[[金融时报_(英国)|金融时报]]》的忠实读者。<ref name=":1" />

1981年至1986年，贾维德在布里斯托尔附近的国立综合学院Downend School受教育，在2014年发表的演讲中，他承认自己在学校时“很顽皮，对观看《{{le|格兰其山|Grange Hill}}》比做作业更感兴趣”。<ref name=":1" />1986年入读{{le|菲尔顿技术学院|South Gloucestershire and Stroud College}}，1988年至1991年在[[埃克塞特大学|埃克塞特大学]]学习经济学和政治学，并成为保守党党员。<ref>[http://www.sajidjavid.com/text.aspx?id=78 Sajid Javid Biography] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715225824/http://www.sajidjavid.com/text.aspx?id=78 |date=2011-07-15 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.sajidjavid.com/upload/The%20Village.pdf Profile of Sajid Javid] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715225748/http://www.sajidjavid.com/upload/The%20Village.pdf |date=2011-07-15 }}</ref><ref>"[http://www.bristolpost.co.uk/news/bristol-news/11-bristol-celebrities-go-school-17024 Where did these 11 Bristol celebrities go to school?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bristolpost.co.uk/news/bristol-news/11-bristol-celebrities-go-school-17024 |date=20170520225052 }}",''Bristol Post'', 2 April 2017 (Accessed 4th April 2017)</ref>

20岁时，贾维德第一次出席{{le|保守党年会|Conservative Party (UK) Conference}}，并且反对{{le|撒切尔政府|Premiership of Margaret Thatcher}}加入[[欧洲汇率机制|欧洲汇率机制]]（ERM）的决定，称之为“致命的错误”。<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=http://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/treasury-minister-sajid-javid-dont-slam-the-city-it-represents-some-of-the-best-of-capitalism-8134667.html|title=Treasury minister Sajid Javid: Don’t slam the City, it represents some of the best of capitalism|work=The Evening Standard|accessdate=2015-01-28|archive-date=2015-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150127191914/http://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/treasury-minister-sajid-javid-dont-slam-the-city-it-represents-some-of-the-best-of-capitalism-8134667.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

大学毕业后贾维德立即[[纽约市|纽约市]]加入[[纽约市|纽约市]]的[[大通银行|大通曼哈顿银行]]，主要在南美洲工作。1993年他作为兼职幕僚帮助[[鲁迪·朱利安尼|鲁迪·朱利安尼]]{{le|1993年纽约市市长选举|New York City mayoral election, 1993|竞选纽约市市长}}。<ref name=javid-usa-guardian>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/apr/11/sajid-javid-a-wonderful-life-banker-culture-minister|title=Sajid Javid's Wonderful Life – from investment banker to culture minister|date=2014-04-11|work=The Guardian|accessdate=2018-08-17|archive-date=2018-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181209114532/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/apr/11/sajid-javid-a-wonderful-life-banker-culture-minister|dead-url=no}}</ref>25岁，{{efn|通常说法是25岁，但保守党官网则称24岁。<ref name="Wall Street">{{cite web |last=Herrmann |first=Joshi |title=What Thatcherite union buster Sajid Javid learned on Wall Street |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/jul/15/sajid-javid-what-thatcherite-union-buster-learned-from-wall-street |website=The Guardian |accessdate=2018-07-31 |date=2015-07-15 |archive-date=2018-07-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180731213233/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/jul/15/sajid-javid-what-thatcherite-union-buster-learned-from-wall-street |dead-url=no }}</ref>其他来源<ref>{{cite web |title=Sajid Javid - profile: the working class Conservative taking over from |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/sajid-javid-profile-the-working-class-conservative-taking-over-from-maria-miller-as-culture-9248545.html |website=The Independent |accessdate=2018-07-31 |archive-date=2018-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801010802/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/sajid-javid-profile-the-working-class-conservative-taking-over-from-maria-miller-as-culture-9248545.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name= javid-telegraph-2015int>{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Mick |title=Sajid Javid: 'Plenty of British Muslims would agree we can no longer be held back by political correctness' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/11509291/Sajid-Javid-Plenty-of-British-Muslims-would-agree-we-can-no-longer-be-held-back-by-political-correctness.html |accessdate=2018-07-31 |date=2015-04-04 |archive-date=2018-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801003655/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/11509291/Sajid-Javid-Plenty-of-British-Muslims-would-agree-we-can-no-longer-be-held-back-by-political-correctness.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>.}}他成为该银行历史上最年轻的副总裁。{{r|"Wall Street"}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nelson |first1=Fraser |title=Sajid Javid: the man who thinks big |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/conservative/10757640/Sajid-Javid-the-man-who-thinks-big.html |accessdate=2018-07-31 |date=2014-04-11 |archive-date=2018-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801003713/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/conservative/10757640/Sajid-Javid-the-man-who-thinks-big.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{efn|A 2012 article says he was actually vice-chairman.<ref name="Dale1012">Iain Dale [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/conservative/9589957/Iain-Dales-Top-100-most-influential-figures-from-the-Right-2012.html "Iain Dale's Top 100 most influential figures from the Right 2012"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/conservative/9589957/Iain-Dales-Top-100-most-influential-figures-from-the-Right-2012.html |date=20121012142918 }}, ''The Daily Telegraph'', 7 October 2012</ref>}}1997年他回到伦敦工作，2000年加入[[德意志银行|德意志银行]]担任[[董事|董事]]。2004年，成为德意志银行的[[首席执行官|董事总经理]]，一年后担任其全球新兴市场结构负责人。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.db.com/medien/en/content/press_releases_2005_2697.htm|title=Deutsche Bank appoints Sajid Javid as Global Head of Emerging Markets Structuring|date=2005-05-27|work=db.com|accessdate=2015-01-28|archive-date=2015-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518155240/https://www.db.com/medien/en/content/press_releases_2005_2697.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2007年，贾维德前往[[新加坡|新加坡]]任德意志银行亚洲区信贷交易、股票可转换债券、商品和私募股权业务负责人，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.db.com/medien/en/content/press_releases_2006_3217.htm|title=Deutsche Bank appoints Sajid Javid Head of Global Credit Trading, Asia|date=2006-10-11|work=db.com|accessdate=2015-01-28|archive-date=2015-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518132848/https://www.db.com/medien/en/content/press_releases_2006_3217.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>并兼任德意志银行国际有限公司董事会成员。2009年离开德意志银行进军[[政治|政坛]]。他在德意志银行的年收入到离职时约为300万英镑。<ref>{{Cite news |last1 = Donaldson |first1 = Kitty |last2 = Hutton |first2 = Robert |date = 2014-04-09 |title = U.K. Treasury's Javid Moves to Culture After Miller Quits |url = https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-04-09/u-k-treasury-s-javid-moves-to-culture-after-miller-quits.html |publisher = [[Bloomberg_L.P.|Bloomberg L.P.]] |accessdate = 2014-04-09 |archive-date = 2014-04-13 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413124547/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-04-09/u-k-treasury-s-javid-moves-to-culture-after-miller-quits.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>《伦敦标准晚报》称他从政后收入减少了98%。<ref name=guardiansjrand>{{cite news|last=Elgot|first=Jessica|date=2018-04-30|title=Who is Sajid Javid, the UK's new home secretary?|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/apr/30/for-sajid-javid-the-hostile-environment-is-political-and-personal|newspaper=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|accessdate=2018-06-06|archive-date=2018-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180430173629/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/apr/30/for-sajid-javid-the-hostile-environment-is-political-and-personal|dead-url=no}}</ref>

贾维德是伦敦Early Years基金会的[[受托人|受托人]]，曾任Normand Croft社区{{le|学校校董|School governor}}，并率领了考察非洲最高山[[乞力马扎罗山|乞力马扎罗山]]的登山队，表示他对公益组织“{{le|帮助老年人|Help the Aged}}”的支持。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sajidjavid.com/text.aspx?id=60 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2011-02-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715225443/http://www.sajidjavid.com/text.aspx?id=60 |archivedate=2011-07-15 }}</ref>

